# Naming Conventions — obm_gen_with_ai

> Variables: See `_project_config.mdc`. Key values: `{{FILE_CASE}}`, `{{CLASS_CASE}}`, `{{BOOL_PREFIX}}`, `{{CALLBACK_PREFIX}}`, `{{ASYNC_METHOD}}`, `{{I18N_CLASS}}`, `{{I18N_GETTER}}`, `{{I18N_FILE_PATTERN}}`, `{{I18N_KEY_STYLE}}`.

## General Principles

- **`{{FILE_CASE}}`** for file and folder names.
- **`{{CLASS_CASE}}`** for class, enum, typedef names.
- **`camelCase`** for variables, methods, parameters.
- Names must be **meaningful** — no vague abbreviations (`btn1`, `data2`).
- English in code; Vietnamese only for user-facing strings via `{{I18N_CLASS}}`.

## File Names (`{{FILE_CASE}}`)

| Type           | Pattern                          | Example                          |
|----------------|----------------------------------|----------------------------------|
| Screen         | `*_screen.dart`                 | `home_screen.dart`               |
| Provider       | `*_provider.dart`               | `home_provider.dart`             |
| Service        | `*_service.dart`                | `home_service.dart`              |
| Model          | `*_model.dart`                  | `home_model.dart`                |
| Body widget    | `body_*_widget.dart`             | `body_home_widget.dart`          |
| Item widget    | `item_*.dart`                   | `item_user.dart`                 |
| Component dir  | `component/`                     | `component/`                     |
| Feature dir    | `features/<feature_name>/`       | `features/home/`                  |
| Sub-dir        | `{component,model,widget}/`    | `features/home/{component,model,widget}/` |

## Class Names (`{{CLASS_CASE}}`)

| Type           | Pattern                          | Example                          |
|----------------|----------------------------------|----------------------------------|
| Screen         | `XxxScreen`                     | `HomeScreen`                    |
| Body widget    | `BodyXxxWidget`                 | `BodyHomeWidget`                |
| Item widget    | `ItemXxx`                       | `ItemUser`                      |
| Provider       | `XxxProvider`                   | `HomeProvider`                  |
| Service        | `XxxService`                    | `HomeService`                    |
| Model          | `XxxModel`                      | `UserModel`                      |
| Request/Resp   | `XxxRequest` / `XxxResponse`   | `LoginRequest` / `LoginResponse` |
| Dialog widget  | `XxxForm` (extends `DialogForm`) | `LoginForm`                    |
| Enum           | `XxxType`                       | `DocumentType`                   |

## Variables & Methods

```dart
// camelCase
String userName = 'An';
bool isLoading = false;
bool showHeader = true;
bool hasPermission = false;
bool enableSubmit = true;

// Provider state fields ({{PROVIDER_BASE}} already provides currentState)
// Multi-operation → separate field
StateType detailState = StateType.none;

// Async
{{ASYNC_METHOD}} fetchItems() async { ... }
```

| Kind                    | Convention                                       |
|-------------------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| Boolean                 | `{{BOOL_PREFIX}}` (`isXxx`, `showXxx`, `hasXxx`, `canXxx`, `enableXxx`) |
| Async method            | `{{ASYNC_METHOD}}` + `async/await`              |
| Callback                | `{{CALLBACK_PREFIX}}` (`onTap`, `onSubmit`, `onRefresh`) |
| Stream subscription     | `_xxxSubscription`                              |
| Controller              | `_xxxController` / `xxxController` (public if needed) |
| Refresh controller      | `refreshController` / `refreshControllerDefault` |

## Routes

```dart
// lib/core/constants/routes.dart  (TODO: create when pushNamed is needed)
class Routes {
  static const String featureName = '/featureName';
}

// Usage
Navigator.pushNamed(context, Routes.featureName, arguments: {...});
```

Route key name: camelCase. Route value: `/camelCase`.

## Localization Keys (`{{I18N_KEY_STYLE}}`)

- Files: `{{I18N_FILE_PATTERN}}`.
- Key format: **`{{I18N_KEY_STYLE}}`** — NO `{{NO_LOCALE_KEYS}}` / `{{NO_PREFIX}}` convention.
- Add a getter to `lib/core/constants/app_strings.dart`:

```dart
class {{I18N_CLASS}} {
  static String get xxxLabel      => 'xxxLabel'.tr();
  static String xxxWithArg(int n) => 'xxxWithArg'.tr(namedArgs: {'n': n.toString()});
}
```

When adding a new string:
1. Add key to all 4 JSON files.
2. Add getter to `{{I18N_CLASS}}`.

## Imports

| Layer               | Path                                                  |
|---------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
| Base / core         | `{{IMPORT_CORE}}`                                      |
| Components          | `{{IMPORT_COMPONENTS}}`                                |
| Constants           | `{{IMPORT_CONSTANTS}}`                                 |
| Utils               | `{{IMPORT_UTIL}}`                                      |
| Feature in same pkg | `{{PACKAGE_IMPORT}}features/<feature>/...`             |

## DO / DON'T

| DO                              | DON'T                                            |
|---------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| `home_screen.dart`               | `HomeScreen.dart`, `homeScreenScreen.dart`       |
| `class HomeScreen`              | `class home_screen`                              |
| `bool isLoading`                | `bool loading`, `bool Loading`                   |
| `bool showXxx`                  | `bool displayXxx`                               |
| `{{ASYNC_METHOD}} fetchItems()` | `Future<void> getItems()` (name clashes with getter) |
| `contextParent: context`         | `contextParrent` (check correct spelling) |

## Review Checklist

- [ ] New file follows `*_screen.dart` / `*_provider.dart` / etc. pattern.
- [ ] Class name is PascalCase.
- [ ] Booleans start with `{{BOOL_PREFIX}}`.
- [ ] Every user-facing string has a key in all 4 JSON files and a getter in `{{I18N_CLASS}}`.
- [ ] Imports follow the layer map above.
- [ ] Callbacks named `{{CALLBACK_PREFIX}}`; subscriptions named `_xxxSubscription`.
